SIMPLE: cementation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cementation
<hw>Cem`en*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act or process of cementing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A process which consists in
surrounding a solid body with the powder of other substances, and
heating the whole to a degree not sufficient to cause fusion, the
physical properties of the body being changed by chemical combination
with powder; thus iron becomes steel by cementation with charcoal, and
green glass becomes porcelain by cementation with sand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cementatory</ent>⟦br⟧
